The '''Atmospheric dynamo''' is a pattern of [[electrical current]]s that are set up in the [[Earth]]'s [[ionosphere]] by multiple effects, mostly the [[Sun]]'s [[solar wind]], but also the [[tide]]s of the [[Moon]] and Sun.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=uVA4AAAAIAAJ&lpg=PA84&ots=bgk_6ndSaD&dq=atmospheric%20dynamo&pg=PA86#v=onepage&q=atmospheric%20dynamo&f=false An introduction to the ionosphere ... - Google Books<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.agu.org/pubs/crossref/1957/JZ062i002p00329.shtml On The Atmospheric Dynamo Theory<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The currents flow in circuits between the [[Geographical pole|poles]] and the [[equator]], but they are not well understood.<ref>[http://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/sunearth/news/rockets-atmosphere.html NASA - Sounding Rockets Study How Winds In Space Drive Currents in the Upper Atmosphere<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

