The '''Bliha''' is a [[river]] in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. It is a left tributary of the [[Sana (river)|Sana]] river, located in region of [[Bosanska Krajina]], on [[Sanski Most]] municipality territory and town vicinity.
==Bliha Falls== {{Main|Bliha Falls}} The [[Bliha Falls]] ({{lang-bs|Vodopad Blihe}}; or {{lang-bs|Slapovi Blihe}}), called by locals ''Blihin Skok'' (''{{lang-en|Bliha's Jump}}'' or ''{{lang-en|Leap of Bliha}}''), is a [[waterfall]] on the Bliha river located near Fajtovci, 14 kilometers west of Sanski Most, Bosnia and Herzegovina. The 56 meters high waterfall is designated a [[natural monument]] since 1965.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanskimost.gov.ba/PDF/TURIZAM%20U%20SM.pdf |title=Sanski Most |language=Bosnian |page=2 |accessdate=15 July 2012 |publisher=Government of Bosnia and Herzegovina}}</ref><ref name=EUNIS>{{cite web|url=http://eunis.eea.europa.eu/sites/179509 |title=Vodopad Bliha |publisher=[[European Environment Agency]] |accessdate=15 July 2012}}</ref>
